  <description type="morphology">Plants light green, not stoloniferous, 0.7–8.2 dm. Stems erect or ascending (rarely
        prostrate). Leaves basal and cauline or all cauline, sessile or petiolate; blade obovate or
        broadly spatulate to elliptic, 1.5–15 cm, base decurrent, cuneate, apex rounded to obtuse.
        Inflorescences terminal or terminal and axillary, usually racemose, sometimes paniculate,
        sessile or pedunculate; peduncle to 0.7 cm, usually shorter (to longer) than stem. Pedicels
        spreading or ascending, bracteate, 1.5–14 mm, glabrous; bract at midlength. Flowers: calyx
        1.3–1.5(–2) mm, lobes triangular to ovate, shorter than tube, apex acute, not glandular;
        corolla white, 1.2–3 mm, lobes oblong, longer than tube, base glabrous, apex rounded or
        emarginate; staminodes 5. Capsules 2–3 mm. 2n = 26.</description>
